# Object storage (experimental)

Default driver is **local** (`public/uploads`). Set these to use an S3-compatible bucket:

```bash
STORAGE_DRIVER=s3
S3_BUCKET=my-bucket
S3_REGION=us-east-1
S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=...
S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...
# Optional
S3_ENDPOINT=https://minio.example.com   # MinIO / R2 / GCS XML API
S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://cdn.example.com
S3_FORCE_PATH_STYLE=true
```

Upload still runs ffmpeg on a local work copy, then publishes progressive / poster / HLS
artifacts through `getObjectStore()`.

# Multi-instance DM fan-out (experimental)

SSE realtime is in-process by default. To share DM events across Node instances:

```bash
REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6379
```

When unset, the app stays on the in-memory conversation bus (single instance).
